I am a creative, reliable, and adaptable graphic designer who strives to achieve excellence and satisfaction in every project.

name: Khaled Mohamed
headline: Software Engineer @ Google | ICPC World Finalist | Founder
creator: True
bio:
I like to build or maybe break stuff using code. I am mostly interested in working on big infrastructures, distributed systems and networking. In most of my roles I got to use my experience with algorithms and data structures to solve real problems.

At Google I worked as a Software Engineer contributing to Data/Privacy Policy infrastructure, we dealt with the problems of data flow / data discovery across Google’s data stores. I was also a Site Reliability Engineer on the Traffic team, the team was responsible for the Layer7 load balancing of Google Cloud.

At Huawei I was working on their Linux based TCP/IP stack and the firmware for some of the low-end routers manufactured by Huawei. I got to implement performance-critical solutions to work with the limitations of those low-end devices.

name: Kim Fom
headline: Software Engineer | C# | .NET
creator: True
bio:
I am a motivated, creative and dedicated software developer with experience in managing multiple tasks simultaneously. My projects can be found on GitHub: https://github.com/kimfom01 . I take an innovative approach to problem solving and always strive for professional growth by learning new skills.

I have extensive experience working with programming languages such as C# and TypeScript, as well as in web development using ASP.NET Core, React.js, Remix, HTML/CSS, and TailwindCSS. I specialize in working with databases (Entity Framework Core, LINQ, SQL Server, PostgreSQL, SQLite) and designing their structure.

I have excellent time management skills and work both as a team and individually. I use version control systems (Git, GitHub, GitLab) and ensure code quality through unit and integration testing. My experience includes containerization with Docker and Docker Compose, server side development (REST API, Swagger, Postman), and workflow automation with GitHub Actions, Cron tasks on Linux, and Bash scripts.

I am confident working in Linux (Ubuntu) and Windows environments and have practical experience in MVC, Redis, RabbitMQ architecture and creating detailed technical documentation. I am always open to new challenges and strive to bring innovative solutions to achieve the goals of the team and the organization.

name: Emeka Nzeopara
headline: Security Engineer @ Wazuh
creator: False
bio:
With a passion for cybersecurity and a drive to learn and innovate, I am a Security Engineer at Innopolis University and a Cyber Security Engineer at Mossé Cyber Security Institute, where I apply my skills and knowledge in various domains of security, cloud, and automation. 

I have a Master's degree in Cybersecurity from Innopolis University, a Nanodegree in Cloud DevOps from Udacity, and a Bachelor of Engineering in Electrical and Electronics Engineering from the University of Benin. I am proficient in multiple technologies and tools, such as Azure Sentinel, AWS and Azure Cloud, Jenkins, CircleCI, Gitlab, Ansible, Terraform, Python, Bash, Docker, and Kubernetes. 

I have experience in network security engineering, SIEM, XDR, IDS/IPS, and endpoint security, and I have contributed to several projects that involved designing, implementing, and maintaining secure and scalable systems and solutions for clients and customers. I have also received multiple certifications in cybersecurity foundations, operationalizing MITRE ATT&CK, and ethical hacking from scratch. 

I am committed to performing and executing the assigned tasks while working in a fast-paced environment, and I am adept at identifying and researching the fastest and most effective ways to achieve the desired outcomes. I am also dedicated to staying current with industry developments and evolving technologies, and to leveraging my technical expertise and education to drive organizational growth and alleviate security concerns
